Object.Field: JKM MSSQL to Teradata Consistent (OGG Online)

COMPONENT NAME: JKM MSSQL to Teradata Consistent (OGG Online)
AUTHOR: Oracle
DESCRIPTION - This JKM provides consistent journalizing procedures for MSSQL tables. - When starting the journal on a model, journals are automatically dropped from tables no longer in the set and new tables in the set are journalized. - If the table is already journalized with another model, its current journal data is lost and the table is transferred to the new CDC set. - When migrating Journalization on the model from another KM to this one, always stop the journal with the previous KM and restart with this one. - This KM provides transactional consistency. This means that when using this JKM, you do not have to define the order of the tables in the "Journalizing tables" tab of the Model Window.
- This JKM uses Oracle GoldenGate to capture data changes on the source tables. Unlike other CDC JKMs -This JKM journalize data in a "staging Teradata Database" not in the source server -"Start Journal" menu option will not actually start journaling. -"Start Journal" menu option creates the CDC framework ie : SNP_CDC Objects and J$ tables and views -"Start Journal" menu option creates Oracle GoldenGate parameters files and readme file -Users should not expect any journaled data until the operations in the readme file have been carried out.
-This JKM provides also oracle GoldenGate parameters files to performe the initial load. -This step is not mandatory, and the inial load can be perfomed with others utilities
REQUIREMENTS Oracle GoldenGate must be installed on both servers (source and staging) Data server Name must be specify on Teradata topology and should be an existing DSN (ODBC connection) on teradata server. Database set-up See the Oracle GoldenGate "Oracle Installation and Setup Guide" for more information on database requirements in particular the chapter Preparing the database for GoldenGate
OPTIONS (Refer to Option descriptions for more information on each option) VALIDATE: Adds extra steps to validate the usage of the KM
LIMITATIONS - When Starting the Journal, users should not expect any journaled data until the operations in the readme file have been carried out. - See the Oracle GoldenGate "Oracle Installation and Setup Guide" for more information
